creator: Sigmund Freud
description:
LibriVox recording of The Interpretation of Dreams by Sigmund Freud.

Read in English by rookieblue; Elicia; Judith Parker; ; Steve C; bala; H. Hubbard; Malone; Matthew Westra; Cynthia Moyer; tealrobin; Lee Smalley; KHand; Pamela Krantz; tonihall; Bobby Li; Kirsten Ferreri; lilbert; John Trevithick; Chiquito Crasto.

A neat book on dream-analysis by the founding father of psychoanalysis. This book is about the inner theater and the workings of the mind in the dreaming state. Covering lot of topics the Austrian psychoanalyst's work on dreams is worth reading for any who would getup with a question mark face, trying to remember the dream they had just moments before they got up and try to understand what message their dream was conveying, if at all it was. (Summary by sidhu177)

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
